{"cursor":"17099","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Social constructivism' is a sociological theory of knowledge that applies the\ngeneral philosophical constructivism into social settings, wherein groups\nconstruct knowledge for one another, collaboratively creating a small culture of\nshared artifacts with shared meanings. When one is immersed within a culture of\nthis sort, one is learning all the time about how to be a part of that culture\non many levels. Its origins are largely attributed to Lev Vygotsky.\n","linknr":226,"url":"Social_constructivism","recorded":1362574784,"links":20,"instances":["education"],"pdf":["http://www.oup.com/uk/orc/bin/9780199285433/jackson_chap06.pdf"],"categories":["Constructivism","Enactive cognition","Sociology index"],"headings":["Social constructivism and social constructionism","Social constructivism and philosophy","Social constructivism, psychology, and religion","Social constructivism and education","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/SNA_segment.png/180px-SNA_segment.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["learning_theory","education"]],"members":["learning_theory"],"related":["Sociological_theory","Knowledge","Constructivist_epistemology","Lev_Vygotsky","Social_constructionism","Affordance","Robert_Rocco_Cottone","Humberto_Maturana","Kenneth_Gergen","Social_learning_theory","Computer-supported_collaborative_learning","Constructivist_epistemology","Educational_psychology","Experiential_learning","Learning_theory_(education)","Teaching_for_social_justice","Epimenides"]}